## Help Output

```bash
PS C:\> bookshelf list --help

DESCRIPTION:
    List all books in a bookshelf

USAGE:
    bookshelf list <BOOKSHELF> [OPTIONS]

EXAMPLES:
    bookshelf list /path/to/bookshelf
    bookshelf list /path/to/bookshelf --details
    bookshelf list /path/to/bookshelf --filter Python
    bookshelf list /path/to/bookshelf --sort size --reverse

ARGUMENTS:
    <BOOKSHELF>    The bookshelf directory containing PDF files

OPTIONS:
    -h, --help             Prints help information
    -f, --filter <FILTER>  Filter books by title (case-insensitive search)
    -d, --details          Show detailed book information including file size, creation date, and page count
    -s, --sort <FIELD>     Sort by: title, size, date, or pages
    -r, --reverse          Reverse the sort order (descending instead of ascending)
```

## Error Scenarios

```bash
# Missing required argument
PS C:\> bookshelf list
Error: Missing required argument 'BOOKSHELF'

# Directory doesn't exist
PS C:\> bookshelf list "C:\NonExistent"
Error: Bookshelf directory does not exist: C:\NonExistent

# Invalid sort field
PS C:\> bookshelf list "C:\Bookshelf" --sort invalid
Error: Invalid sort field: invalid. Valid options: title, size, date, pages

# No filter matches
